reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cleans well, rinses well, feels good, looks good.
reviews.reviewText: I am pleasantly surprised by this face wash. Normally, face products with minty, menthol type ingredients cling to my skin and cause irritation, no matter how hard I try to rinse it off. But this face wash is formulated nicely. It rinses off very well and leaves my skin feeling clean, refreshed, healthy-looking and never dried out. It is a very thin liquid, so squeeze the tube slowly and carefully. I find that a little goes a long way. Yeah, this is a nice find. Glad I took a chance. And If exfoliation is part of your routine, this product, and a quality, natural loofah, work great together. Hydréa London Organic Egyptian Loofah Spa Pad is the one I like.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love this face wash!
reviews.reviewText: It's cleanses very well and delicately and leaves your skin feeling refreshed and smelling nice! I'm happy! :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This cooling post shave is a very good product at a great price
reviews.reviewText: This product cools and conditions my skin after shaving with absolutely no oily or greasy feeling. It relieves redness,and leaves my skin looking and feeling soft and clear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Close comfortable shave without lingering scent.
reviews.reviewText: We have many allergies and sensitivities in our house, so scent during use and lingering after use are as important as comfortable shave. The scent in Pacific Shaving cream is citrusy in use but washes off completely. The cream is very lubricating and slippery even after going over an area twice or three times. The second choice Andalou is identical in comfort and closeness. The scent is subtle and also washes away completely. Neutrogena was my go to, is unavailable now, but I would have replaced with either of the first two as it isn’t as close a shave and the scent lingers. I will NEVER buy Vanicream again. The shave is similar to the first two, but the scent makes me gag so much that I want to vomit. And I have changed many diapers and cleaned up lots of vomit without any issues!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Replacement for my normal discontinued product!
reviews.reviewText: I've been on the hunt for a replacement shave cream ever since Every Man Jack discontinued their product. I have tried so many different brands and this was the closest I could come to my previous product.Although I don't care for the pine essentials oil smell while shaving, the product does a good job without irritating my face, and it gives me a close smooth shave. I have two other brands on my list to try, but I don't think I'm going to look any further

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A truly smooth shave from using this cream and a good quality razor!
reviews.reviewText: I have serious problems with the long lingering fragrances in most shaving products, both for myself and the ones my husband uses. The menthol odor in this cream is "wake up refreshing" and does not linger afterwards like the smell of most products. It washes off, but leaves the skin very soft and smooth. And the price is reasonable!As an aside: We use Harry's razors and blades, but I suspect this cream would improve shaving experience with other high quality razors and blades also. I stopped using disposable blades after finding that every brand I tried nicked and cut my skin badly.I know that Andalou also makes some "flavors" of shave cream for women, but this one suits both of us very well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Has been a good go-to. I have tested many shaving creams and lotions and found this one to be near the top. I keep buying more, so I must like it. It does not lather, so if you are a brush guy this won't do. I'm used to shaving without a mirror, so I have no idea what it looks like on my face. But it performs well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My go-to for shaving
reviews.reviewText: I have used this for years. It’s “for men” but I prefer it to all of the other womens products I’ve tried.
It is so good for the skin.. it has moisture and is very soft

reviews.reviewTitle: Best shaving cream I've ever used
reviews.reviewText: No skin irritation AT ALL. Does not leave a residue or dry out your hands or face (hands because that's what I use to make the lather and put it on my face). Very happy with this product!

I bought this to try something different from shaving with soap and brush. On balance, I decided not to use it.Pros: makes for a nice smooth shave; a tube will likely last a long time because it doesn't take much if you follow the directionsCons: have to keep wetting my face to keep it moist; leaves cream on my razor blade no matter how well I rinse it afterward- this is the main reason for the 3 star rating. If you have a 2 or 3 part razor you will have to take it apart to clean it after each shave
Zero issues with this cream. Good glide, no irritation. It’s not a foamy one however if you’re looking for that. I don’t like foam personally as I can’t see what I’m doing and I use safety blades.
Husband loves this line of skin carePrice is goodNo synthetic scentGentle on the skin
